cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL 

This paper deals with the analysis of diachronic text corpora, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a new measure for modeling the degree of semantic change in terms, which involves statistical significance and co-occurrence ranks, indicating a possible connection to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Deep Learning (cs.DL) subcategories.
